        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;"><strong>Embeddings in Natural Language Processing</strong></p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">Mohammad Taher Pilehvar and Jose Camacho-Collados publicly released their first draft of an upcoming <a href="http://josecamachocollados.com/book_embNLP_draft.pdf" target="_self">book</a> called ‚ÄúEmbeddings in Natural Language Processing‚Äù. The idea with this book is to discuss the concept of embeddings which represent some of the most widely used techniques in NLP. As <a href="https://twitter.com/CamachoCollados/status/1246013768074747906?s=20" target="_self">stated</a> by the authors, the book includes ‚Äúbasics in vector space models and word embeddings to more recent sentence and contextualized embedding techniques based on pre-trained language models.‚Äù</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;"><strong>A Brief Guide to Artificial Intelligence</strong></p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">Dr. James V Stone recently published his new <a href="https://jim-stone.staff.shef.ac.uk/AIGuide/" target="_self">book</a> on ‚ÄúA Brief Guide to Artificial Intelligence‚Äù with the goal to provide a comprehensive overview of current AI systems and their achievement to perform a series of tasks. As stated in the summary, the book is ‚Äúwritten in an informal style, with a comprehensive glossary and a list of further readings, which makes it an ideal introduction to the rapidly evolving field of AI.‚Äù</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="image3 cid-tt612oXwA9" id="image3-5" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
